WEBVTT

00:02.176 --> 00:04.613
Griffin: <i>
Previously on</i>Secrets
of Sulphur Springs...

00:04.787 --> 00:06.615
♪ ♪

00:06.789 --> 00:08.573
-What are you doing here, Dad?
-You shouldn't be here, Bennett.

00:08.747 --> 00:09.922
None of you should.

00:10.097 --> 00:11.272
Griffin: <i>
My grandpa being here,</i>

00:11.446 --> 00:13.665
my dad's acting even
weirder than usual.

00:13.839 --> 00:15.754
I know that you asked Harper
to stay away from Griffin.

00:15.928 --> 00:17.191
I think it makes sense
to keep them apart.

00:17.365 --> 00:18.844
At least for now.

00:19.019 --> 00:20.803
Zoey:
This is where we felt
one of the cold spots.

00:20.977 --> 00:22.718
We're gonna finally
catch that ghost in here.

00:23.371 --> 00:25.938
Zoey: <i>
No one else believes us
about Savannah's ghost.</i>

00:26.113 --> 00:27.288
Topher: <i>
That's what the camera's for?</i>

00:28.985 --> 00:31.466
-Your funeral.
-Young Ben: <i>Savannah's
different, you know?</i>

00:31.640 --> 00:33.337
Of course,
not everyone appreciates that.

00:33.511 --> 00:35.426
Young Jess: <i>
I just think this place</i>

00:35.600 --> 00:37.950
would be a whole lot
nicer if she'd just...

00:38.125 --> 00:39.517
-go away.
-Harper [on phone]: <i>
Griffin,</i>

00:39.691 --> 00:41.780
my mom didn't just
hate Savannah.

00:41.954 --> 00:43.086
She acted on it
at the talent show.

00:43.260 --> 00:45.306
And the winner is Ben Campbell!

00:45.480 --> 00:47.743
[light applause]

00:47.917 --> 00:50.224
Harper [on phone]: <i>
I think she might've actually
done something to Savannah.</i>

00:50.398 --> 00:52.356
Harper Marie,
you skipped school today?

00:52.530 --> 00:54.880
-I just got off the phone with
your principal. You're grounded.
-Grounded.

00:55.055 --> 00:57.274
Young Ben: <i>
Last big camp event of
the summer. Should be fun.</i>

00:57.448 --> 01:00.321
-I was thinking of skipping it.
-You have to be there. Trust me.

01:01.061 --> 01:03.019
It'll be a night to... remember.

01:03.193 --> 01:06.588
♪ ♪

01:07.893 --> 01:10.331
-Meteorologist [on TV]: <i>
...highs around 90 degrees.</i>

01:10.505 --> 01:13.160
<i>-Overnight lows in
the 50s initially,
-[banging]</i>

01:13.334 --> 01:16.598
<i>bumping up again
towards 70 degrees. <i>
Looks like a chance</i></i>

01:16.772 --> 01:18.426
<i>for spotty rain will
continue throughout the day</i>

01:18.600 --> 01:20.950
<i>with a chance of thunderstorms <i>until around 9:00 tonight,</i></i>

01:21.124 --> 01:22.691
<i>so don't forget your umbrella.</i>

01:22.865 --> 01:25.259
<i>Thanks, Marla.
Today marks the anniversary</i>

01:25.433 --> 01:27.478
<i>of one of Sulphur Springs'
most notorious</i>

01:27.652 --> 01:30.090
<i>unsolved mysteries.
Savannah Dillon</i>

01:30.264 --> 01:31.830
<i>disappeared
30 years ago tonight</i>

01:32.004 --> 01:34.529
<i>following a camp dance at
the historic Tremont Hotel.</i>

01:34.703 --> 01:37.227
<i>Dillon's disappearance
set off a parish-wide search</i>

01:37.401 --> 01:39.838
<i>-involving multiple law
enforcement agencies.
-[click]</i>

01:40.012 --> 01:42.798
♪ ♪

01:47.368 --> 01:48.586
[thunder rumbling]

01:52.199 --> 01:54.288
Man, I've never been in such
a hurry for school to be over.

01:54.462 --> 01:56.725
Me either. I just kept
thinking about Savannah.

01:56.899 --> 01:58.161
What time is it?

01:59.380 --> 02:01.773
It's 3:15. The camp
dance starts at 8:00.

02:01.947 --> 02:03.688
That gives us less than
five hours to go back

02:03.862 --> 02:05.734
and try and save her from...

02:05.908 --> 02:06.996
♪ ♪

02:07.170 --> 02:08.040
Just say it. My mom.

02:08.215 --> 02:09.477
We don't know that for sure.

02:09.651 --> 02:11.522
Either way, you'll have
to keep an eye on her

02:11.696 --> 02:13.481
-if I can't make it.
-Wait, what? You have to come.

02:13.655 --> 02:15.831
I'll try,
but it's gonna be tough.

02:16.005 --> 02:17.615
I mean,
I am super grounded.

02:17.789 --> 02:19.922
So, now I have to keep
an eye out on your mom,

02:20.096 --> 02:22.577
Savannah, and anyone else who
looks like they're gonna try

02:22.751 --> 02:24.013
-and do something bad to her?
-Possibly.

02:25.449 --> 02:27.495
That stinks. We're better
together, you know?

02:30.846 --> 02:32.021
As a team, I mean.

02:32.195 --> 02:33.849
I know what you mean.

02:34.937 --> 02:35.633
[car honk]

02:37.200 --> 02:39.202
-Harper!
-One second!

02:39.376 --> 02:40.899
-Now!
-[honking]

02:41.073 --> 02:42.162
Griffin!

02:42.771 --> 02:44.033
Griffin:
Wow.

02:44.207 --> 02:46.340
-It's like they're a team now.
-Harper: Remember,

02:46.514 --> 02:48.255
if I can't make it,
you have to go back, okay?

02:48.429 --> 02:49.778
We have to
save Savannah.

02:51.910 --> 02:53.129
♪ ♪

02:53.303 --> 02:56.263
[theme song playing]

03:19.024 --> 03:20.896
[footsteps approaching]

03:21.070 --> 03:23.420
Why did I let Kirsten talk me
into hosting this open mic

03:23.594 --> 03:25.683
-at the shop?
-She's a very persuasive woman.

03:25.857 --> 03:26.945
Jess:
This is true.

03:27.119 --> 03:29.948
I'm late.
Oh, before I forget.

03:30.906 --> 03:31.863
♪ ♪

03:32.037 --> 03:33.909
What's this?

03:34.083 --> 03:36.128
Your sister is going through
a challenging time right now.

03:36.303 --> 03:38.609
She's... rebelling a bit.

03:39.306 --> 03:40.959
You're putting me in charge?

03:41.133 --> 03:43.745
I'm asking you to keep
an eye on her, okay?

03:43.919 --> 03:46.226
She leaves this house for
any reason, you call me.

03:47.531 --> 03:50.273
Consider it... done.

03:54.495 --> 03:56.497
And clean up this mess, huh?

04:00.718 --> 04:02.503
[door opens, shuts]

04:05.288 --> 04:06.420
Did I just hear Mom leave?

04:08.422 --> 04:10.902
-You must have
excellent hearing.
-Harper: Did she say

04:11.076 --> 04:13.122
-when she'd be back?
-Topher: No.

04:13.296 --> 04:15.342
Why? Going somewhere?

04:15.516 --> 04:16.430
No.

04:18.214 --> 04:20.825
Okay, let's say I do
have someplace to be.

04:20.999 --> 04:22.436
-What's it gonna cost me?
-What've you got?

04:22.610 --> 04:25.047
Uh... 20 bucks,

04:25.221 --> 04:26.744
and my Scream Stream password.

04:26.918 --> 04:28.398
But you have to really
cover for me, okay?

04:29.094 --> 04:30.574
Hm...

04:30.748 --> 04:33.185
-That is enticing.
-Just think.

04:33.360 --> 04:36.101
All those super scary zombie
flicks Mom won't let you watch.

04:36.276 --> 04:39.801
-You'll be having
nightmares for weeks.
-Sounds great.

04:39.975 --> 04:41.193
♪ ♪

04:41.368 --> 04:43.326
Nice doing business with you.

04:46.198 --> 04:47.896
[birds chirping]

04:54.250 --> 04:56.208
There you are.
What took you so long?

04:56.383 --> 04:57.819
I had to wait for Mom
to leave the kitchen.

04:57.993 --> 04:58.994
Parsley?

04:59.603 --> 05:02.171
Rosemary? I told you.

05:02.345 --> 05:04.652
We need sage to cleanse
the hotel of Savannah's spirit.

05:05.305 --> 05:08.569
I know, but we're out.
So I thought I'd substitute.

05:08.743 --> 05:11.398
-Chipotle mayo?
-That's a spice!

05:11.572 --> 05:14.357
It's a condiment!
Wyatt, this is important.

05:14.531 --> 05:16.620
I saw it on the news!

05:16.794 --> 05:19.231
Tonight's the anniversary
of Savannah's disappearance,

05:19.406 --> 05:22.496
which means she'll probably be
haunting this place extra hard.

05:22.670 --> 05:24.889
So, if we don't have sage,

05:25.063 --> 05:26.064
why don't we try something else?

05:26.238 --> 05:28.893
-Like what?
-Well,

05:29.067 --> 05:30.634
I guess we could always
give her something.

05:31.374 --> 05:33.507
Yes! Like a peace offering!

05:34.856 --> 05:37.119
But, what kind of things
did Savannah like?

05:37.293 --> 05:40.340
I don't know,
but it better be cheap.

05:40.514 --> 05:42.211
I only have
eight dollars and 74 cents.

05:42.820 --> 05:45.170
That's okay.
We'll find some good stuff.

05:46.171 --> 05:49.174
♪ ♪

05:57.400 --> 06:00.142
[chains rattling]

06:01.099 --> 06:03.537
[creaking]

06:05.190 --> 06:06.888
-[clang]
-[chains rattle]

06:14.939 --> 06:16.898
-[whooshing]
-Ah!

06:17.072 --> 06:18.813
Dude, I don't think I'm ever
gonna get used to that.

06:19.727 --> 06:22.773
-[sighs]
-Dude, did you really
just call yourself dude?

06:22.947 --> 06:25.341
-Uh, yeah, I guess I did.
-[laughs]

06:25.515 --> 06:27.387
Don't feel bad.
You don't wanna know what
I said when I felt it.

06:27.561 --> 06:29.258
-[Griffin grunts]
-[bangs]

06:29.432 --> 06:30.781
Hurry up. We don't
have much time.

06:30.955 --> 06:32.043
The dance is gonna start soon.

06:32.217 --> 06:34.002
[creaking]

06:35.960 --> 06:38.136
♪ ♪

06:38.310 --> 06:40.574
Griffin:
All the reports say Savannah
went missing after the dance,

06:40.748 --> 06:43.490
but they didn't
say how soon after.

06:43.664 --> 06:45.927
Right, so all we have
to do is stay with her

06:46.101 --> 06:47.668
until we're positive
she's safe in her bunk,

06:47.842 --> 06:49.365
while keeping
an eye on Jess.

06:49.539 --> 06:51.149
Or anyone else
suspicious.

06:51.323 --> 06:53.717
Preferably before my mom gets
home from work and grounds me

06:53.891 --> 06:55.676
-until I'm 28.
-You make it sound so easy.

06:56.328 --> 06:58.722
[laughs] Wait,

06:58.896 --> 07:00.811
If they're both
going to the dance,

07:00.985 --> 07:03.466
-we can't crash
dressed like this.
-Don't worry, we're covered.

07:03.640 --> 07:06.077
-I even brought you something.
-[opens bag]

07:06.730 --> 07:08.819
A tie?

07:08.993 --> 07:11.169
-With vampires on it?
-It's Topher's,

07:11.343 --> 07:13.520
but we won't even need it
if we can somehow

07:13.694 --> 07:16.305
-convince Savannah
to skip the dance.
-Oh! Yeah.

07:16.479 --> 07:18.655
-I had an idea on that.
-[unzips bag]

07:20.962 --> 07:23.834
-A tablet? There's no
Wi-Fi here, remember?
-I know.

07:24.661 --> 07:26.620
Before I left, I downloaded
a video of the local news

07:26.794 --> 07:28.143
from the day
Savannah went missing.

07:28.317 --> 07:30.275
-When she sees it...
-You think she'll believe it?

07:30.450 --> 07:32.626
Of course.
How can we fake
an entire news report?

07:33.496 --> 07:35.280
Good point.

07:35.455 --> 07:37.108
But in case she freaks out, be
gentle when you show it to her.

07:37.282 --> 07:39.328
Me? Why do I have to do it?

07:39.502 --> 07:41.504
Because I'll be too
busy watching my mom.

07:41.678 --> 07:44.246
♪ ♪

07:44.420 --> 07:46.596
[birds chirping]

07:51.340 --> 07:52.297
[Jess sighs]

07:55.213 --> 07:58.173
If you're looking for
Savannah, she's not here.

07:59.566 --> 08:01.698
Uh, no, actually.

08:01.872 --> 08:03.961
I was passing by
and thought I'd say hey.

08:07.138 --> 08:10.141
Why would you do that?
We're not friends.

08:11.055 --> 08:14.058
I know. I just
wanted to say, uh...

08:15.016 --> 08:18.019
That's a pretty dress.
Big dance tonight, huh?

08:18.976 --> 08:21.022
-Highlight of the summer.
-You look great.

08:22.023 --> 08:23.590
Although...

08:24.242 --> 08:25.635
Although?

08:25.809 --> 08:28.551
-Nothing. Just your makeup.
-What about it?

08:29.247 --> 08:31.293
Tiny suggestion.

08:31.467 --> 08:34.601
-[opens bag]
-It's called Berry Bliss.

08:34.775 --> 08:36.907
Something tells me
it'll look amazing on you.

08:37.081 --> 08:38.692
♪ ♪

08:38.866 --> 08:41.390
-Never heard of it.
-It's new.

08:41.564 --> 08:43.610
Like, really new. [laughs]

08:49.746 --> 08:52.749
I just figured with your
complexion and that dress,

08:52.923 --> 08:54.795
it would go amazing.

08:54.969 --> 08:57.275
-[laughs] Wow!
-[caps lipstick]

08:57.449 --> 08:59.103
Where'd you get this?

08:59.495 --> 09:01.758
-My mom, actually.
-I love it.

09:03.630 --> 09:05.849
Hey, Hermione, um...

09:06.023 --> 09:07.503
do you wanna come to
the dance with me tonight?

09:08.025 --> 09:09.897
Yeah! Sure! Uh,

09:10.071 --> 09:12.073
I think I even have
something to wear.

09:12.247 --> 09:14.075
But, why me?

09:14.249 --> 09:16.207
Like you said,
we're not friends.

09:17.774 --> 09:19.515
Well...

09:19.689 --> 09:20.821
we're not friends yet.

09:25.260 --> 09:28.524
Besides, I can always use
a partner in... crime.

09:34.225 --> 09:37.228
♪ ♪

09:41.493 --> 09:42.538
[clears throat]

09:44.366 --> 09:47.021
Mom. You're home early.

09:47.195 --> 09:48.413
Yeah. Kirsten
offered to close up.

09:48.588 --> 09:49.632
Where's your sister?

09:50.938 --> 09:52.940
In her room, asleep.

09:53.897 --> 09:55.769
Guess all that misbehavior
kinda wore her out.

09:55.943 --> 09:57.814
Hm, I see.

09:57.988 --> 09:59.860
Well, maybe I'll just
pop in and say goodnight.

10:00.425 --> 10:02.906
Oh. Okay.

10:03.080 --> 10:04.691
-Good night.
-Good night.

10:05.517 --> 10:07.563
[door creaks]

10:07.737 --> 10:10.740
♪ ♪

10:11.872 --> 10:13.525
[snoring]

10:14.962 --> 10:17.268
-[door creaks, shuts]
-[snoring]

10:19.140 --> 10:21.621
[snoring on speaker]

10:22.491 --> 10:25.146
-Wyatt: So that's it?
-Zoey: I guess so.

10:25.320 --> 10:27.583
I just wish we knew more
about what she liked.

10:27.757 --> 10:30.238
Well, everybody likes
money and cheese.

10:31.413 --> 10:34.764
And that '90s guy
is pretty cute.

10:35.722 --> 10:38.550
Whatever.
So, what do we do now?

10:40.248 --> 10:41.205
We wait.

10:45.688 --> 10:47.559
♪ ♪

10:47.734 --> 10:50.693
[birds, insects chirping]

11:00.355 --> 11:03.445
-[thud, scrape]
-[grunts]

11:03.619 --> 11:05.708
-[ladder rattling]
-Griffin: Hey.

11:07.188 --> 11:08.580
Hey, Harry.

11:08.755 --> 11:10.713
How'd you get here?

11:10.887 --> 11:12.236
Nobody knows
about this place.

11:13.498 --> 11:15.675
I, uh, I saw you a little
while ago by the springs,

11:15.849 --> 11:17.502
and I followed you here.

11:17.677 --> 11:20.201
-Okay...
-Listen,

11:20.375 --> 11:21.419
there's something
you need to see.

11:23.030 --> 11:25.380
-It's a--
-Cool! What is that?

11:25.554 --> 11:28.383
Is it a video game?
Can you play Dragon Blaster?

11:28.557 --> 11:30.211
-Or Laser Patrol!
-Savannah.

11:30.385 --> 11:31.647
-[sighs]
-Hey!

11:31.821 --> 11:34.171
Just watch it, okay?

11:36.173 --> 11:37.435
[Savannah sighs]

11:37.609 --> 11:39.089
Oh no.

11:39.263 --> 11:40.961
No, no, no, no.

11:42.049 --> 11:44.616
-What's wrong?
-I think the battery's dead.

11:44.791 --> 11:47.097
That's okay. They sell
batteries at the gift shop.

11:47.271 --> 11:49.099
What kind does it take?
Double A?

11:49.273 --> 11:51.667
-D?
-It's not that kind
of battery, okay?

11:51.841 --> 11:53.756
Harry, relax.

11:53.930 --> 11:56.150
It's just a toy.
It's not like someone just died.

11:57.064 --> 11:59.196
Well, not yet, anyway.

11:59.370 --> 12:02.678
♪ ♪

12:02.852 --> 12:04.332
[footsteps approaching]

12:06.638 --> 12:08.858
I see you finally decided
to fix that window.

12:09.032 --> 12:11.034
Yep. Good as new.

12:11.208 --> 12:13.471
Just as long as you don't
try to open it. Ever.

12:13.645 --> 12:15.169
-[laughs]
-[guitar strumming]

12:15.343 --> 12:17.388
Griff's getting pretty
good on that guitar, huh?

12:17.562 --> 12:19.260
Yeah, he really is.

12:20.217 --> 12:21.958
But I'm worried
about him, Ben.

12:22.132 --> 12:23.481
We pulled him away from
all of his friends,

12:23.655 --> 12:24.831
and now that he has a new one...

12:25.005 --> 12:27.224
We're telling him he
can't see her anymore.

12:29.661 --> 12:31.489
-Think we should go talk to him?
-In a little while.

12:31.663 --> 12:33.100
I'd hate to interrupt his jam.

12:33.274 --> 12:36.103
[guitar continues]

12:36.277 --> 12:38.453
He really is
getting pretty good.

12:38.627 --> 12:41.325
[guitar strumming]

12:50.595 --> 12:53.642
♪ ♪

12:55.339 --> 12:57.080
I just don't get
what the big deal is.

12:57.254 --> 12:58.865
[ladder rattling]

12:59.039 --> 13:00.475
Savannah,
there you are.

13:01.563 --> 13:03.826
Hey, Harry.

13:04.000 --> 13:05.915
The dance is about to start.
You're coming, right?

13:07.656 --> 13:08.875
No, I don't think so.

13:09.614 --> 13:11.355
Exactly!

13:11.529 --> 13:13.183
Camp dances
are pretty stupid.

13:13.357 --> 13:15.055
Is this about that
thing that Jess said?

13:15.795 --> 13:16.970
You know she was kidding, right?

13:17.971 --> 13:20.712
-What'd she say?
-It was so dramatic.

13:20.887 --> 13:22.323
She was talking about the dance.

13:22.671 --> 13:24.934
"It'll be a night to...

13:25.108 --> 13:26.762
remember." [laughs]

13:27.284 --> 13:28.764
Young Ben:
Hey, that sounds just like her.

13:28.938 --> 13:30.244
Please come.
Just for a little while.

13:30.418 --> 13:32.594
♪ ♪

13:32.768 --> 13:35.902
Fine. But only
for a little bit.
Later, Harry.

13:38.121 --> 13:40.036
-Take me with you!
-To the dance?

13:40.515 --> 13:41.777
Yeah!

13:41.951 --> 13:43.779
But you just said
it was stupid.

13:43.953 --> 13:45.781
And it is.

13:45.955 --> 13:48.305
But, the thing is, I'm...

13:48.871 --> 13:50.917
kind of an awesome...

13:51.091 --> 13:53.310
dancer.

13:53.484 --> 13:56.009
And you're looking for some
place to show off your moves.

13:56.748 --> 13:58.359
Uh-huh.

14:00.013 --> 14:03.190
Uh, okay. Sure. Come on.

14:03.364 --> 14:05.105
Let's go.

14:05.279 --> 14:06.933
I can't wait to see these moves.

14:08.804 --> 14:10.501
Yeah.

14:10.675 --> 14:12.155
Me neither.

14:12.808 --> 14:15.550
[heavy breathing]

14:15.724 --> 14:18.118
♪ ♪

14:29.956 --> 14:32.959
[breathing continues]

14:38.225 --> 14:39.574
♪ ♪

14:44.405 --> 14:45.841
-[children chattering]
-[music playing]

14:46.015 --> 14:48.452
[chatter continues]

14:54.110 --> 14:56.765
Wow. Good thing you
decided to pack that dress.

14:56.939 --> 14:59.202
Yeah. Just lucky, I guess.

14:59.376 --> 15:01.378
Um, this place
looks great.

15:01.552 --> 15:02.989
Looked much
better last year

15:03.163 --> 15:04.686
when I was on the
decorating committee.

15:06.818 --> 15:08.777
[inaudible]

15:10.910 --> 15:12.302
Harper:
What is she doing here?

15:12.476 --> 15:14.043
And... [scoffs]

15:14.217 --> 15:16.002
what is she wearing?

15:16.176 --> 15:18.874
Listen, Jess,
you're not planning on

15:19.048 --> 15:20.876
doing anything tonight, are you?

15:21.746 --> 15:23.226
-Like what?
-I don't know.

15:23.400 --> 15:24.967
Anything weird?

15:26.447 --> 15:28.405
You're the one
being weird, Hermione.

15:28.579 --> 15:31.843
-Don't make me
regret bringing you.
-Sorry.

15:32.018 --> 15:34.716
-[inaudible]
-So, um, you gonna
ask Ben to dance?

15:35.978 --> 15:38.067
Please. I'd never ask a guy to
dance this early in the night.

15:38.763 --> 15:39.808
Trust me.

15:41.375 --> 15:44.508
When I'm ready for us
to dance, we'll dance.

15:46.510 --> 15:47.772
Uh, okay.

15:47.947 --> 15:49.905
[music continues]

15:51.428 --> 15:52.690
Griffin, what is
Savannah doing here?

15:52.864 --> 15:54.170
Didn't you show
her the report?

15:54.344 --> 15:56.216
Yeah, I tried,
but the battery was dead.

15:56.390 --> 15:57.521
You forgot to
charge the tablet?

15:57.695 --> 15:59.697
No, I swear!

15:59.871 --> 16:01.743
Something must've happened when
it went through the portal.

16:02.309 --> 16:05.312
-The jolt.
-Yeah. There's more.

16:05.486 --> 16:07.488
Jess made some creepy
comment to Savannah

16:07.662 --> 16:09.969
about how tonight's gonna
be a night to remember.

16:10.143 --> 16:12.319
Makes sense.
She practically told me

16:12.493 --> 16:14.712
she was planning
to do something to her.

16:14.886 --> 16:16.845
She's got something
in this bag.

16:17.019 --> 16:18.760
-Like what?
-I don't know.

16:18.934 --> 16:21.023
She didn't show me. Anyway,
I better get back to her.

16:21.197 --> 16:23.373
Anything else I should know?

16:23.547 --> 16:24.984
Young Ben:
Hey, Harry! There he is!

16:25.158 --> 16:26.681
Let's see those moves.

16:28.161 --> 16:30.990
Yeah. Apparently,
I'm an amazing dancer.

16:31.164 --> 16:32.817
Come on!
Let's see it!

16:32.992 --> 16:35.168
-I don't know, guys.
Maybe later.
-Young Ben: No way, dude.

16:35.342 --> 16:36.386
We even picked
a song just for you.

16:36.560 --> 16:37.561
[dance music playing]

16:37.735 --> 16:40.303
Both:
Go Harry. Go Harry. Go Harry.

16:40.477 --> 16:43.698
All:

16:43.872 --> 16:45.569
Go Harry! Go Harry! Go Harry!

16:45.743 --> 16:48.703
[trailing off]

16:48.877 --> 16:50.574
<i>♪ Do what I want,
who will say I can't ♪</i>

16:50.748 --> 16:53.186
<i>♪ Feel so good,
I'ma do my dance ♪</i>

16:53.360 --> 16:54.883
Is he okay?

16:55.057 --> 16:56.493
Give him a chance.
Maybe he'll get better.

16:56.667 --> 16:58.495
<i>♪ Let me share a little
something with you ♪</i>

16:58.669 --> 17:00.019
Or maybe not.

17:00.193 --> 17:02.499
<i>♪ I'm feeling like
y'all can't move ♪</i>

17:02.673 --> 17:04.675
<i>♪ I'm feeling like
y'all can't lose ♪</i>

17:04.849 --> 17:06.112
<i>♪ I'm feeling like... ♪</i>

17:06.286 --> 17:07.722
Savannah:
[laughs] Nice try.

17:07.896 --> 17:09.550
[song ends]

17:10.681 --> 17:12.205
[laughs] Keep practicing, Harry.

17:14.163 --> 17:15.991
Hey, that's okay.

17:16.165 --> 17:17.253
No time for
dancing anyway.

17:17.427 --> 17:18.994
[sighs]

17:19.168 --> 17:20.822
I'll keep an eye on Savannah.
You go find Jess.

17:20.996 --> 17:23.999
♪ ♪

17:24.869 --> 17:26.262
[burps]

17:27.133 --> 17:28.482
Savannah?

17:29.700 --> 17:32.094
You burped in your sleep.

17:32.268 --> 17:33.965
I didn't know that
was even possible.

17:34.749 --> 17:36.011
Oh.

17:36.968 --> 17:38.709
Guess we shouldn't have
eaten all that cheese.

17:39.623 --> 17:41.756
You shouldn't have
eaten all that cheese.

17:42.844 --> 17:43.627
So, she didn't come?

17:43.801 --> 17:45.803
Not yet anyway.

17:46.761 --> 17:48.110
Too bad.

17:49.068 --> 17:50.417
Oh well.

17:50.982 --> 17:52.375
-I'm going to bed.
-You know, Wyatt.

17:53.376 --> 17:54.943
-Yeah?
-I was thinking.

17:55.117 --> 17:57.337
Maybe you should
sleep here tonight.

17:58.599 --> 18:00.383
I mean, since it's
the anniversary

18:00.557 --> 18:02.646
of Savannah's disappearance
and everything.

18:03.256 --> 18:05.475
Okay. But, just for tonight.

18:05.649 --> 18:08.348
[dance music playing]

18:10.480 --> 18:11.568
Dance is practically
over, huh?

18:11.742 --> 18:13.875
-[inaudible]
-[party chatter]

18:14.049 --> 18:16.573
Guess it's almost time for you
guys to head back to the bunks.

18:16.747 --> 18:19.141
What? No! Light's out isn't

18:19.315 --> 18:21.143
for another hour.
Besides...

18:23.580 --> 18:24.973
it's time.

18:29.978 --> 18:30.892
♪ ♪

18:31.066 --> 18:32.415
Side A, please.

18:34.852 --> 18:35.940
[clicks]

18:38.465 --> 18:39.901
[slow dance song playing]

18:40.075 --> 18:41.859
<i>♪ Everybody's asking ♪</i>

18:43.252 --> 18:45.428
<i>♪ Who I will be ♪</i>

18:46.995 --> 18:49.302
I love this song.
Do you wanna dance?

18:49.476 --> 18:51.217
Hey, why not?

18:51.391 --> 18:54.350
<i>♪ Making predictions on ♪</i>

18:54.524 --> 18:57.092
<i>♪ Where I'll live ♪</i>

18:58.224 --> 18:59.964
<i>♪ Ah... ♪</i>

19:02.402 --> 19:04.752
<i>♪ And make it last ♪</i>

19:04.926 --> 19:06.971
<i>♪ Drive it fast ♪</i>

19:07.146 --> 19:09.409
-Griffin.
-Yeah. I saw.

19:09.583 --> 19:12.020
Your mom is not happy.
You really think she's gonna try

19:12.194 --> 19:13.674
-and pull something?
-I don't know,

19:13.848 --> 19:16.198
but we better stay close to
Savannah in case she does.

19:16.372 --> 19:18.113
How? She's out
there dancing.

19:18.287 --> 19:19.680
How do you think? Come on.

19:21.856 --> 19:24.250
♪ ♪

19:28.079 --> 19:30.299
-Still can't believe I pulled
off those dance moves.
-Yeah.

19:30.473 --> 19:31.996
I'm pretty sure this
is more your speed.

19:33.998 --> 19:36.392
<i>♪ I don't know, I don't know
where I'm going to ♪</i>

19:36.566 --> 19:39.308
<i>♪ All I know is I'm getting
on a train soon ♪</i>

19:39.482 --> 19:41.919
<i>♪ I don't know, I don't know
where I'm going to ♪</i>

19:42.093 --> 19:44.444
♪ ♪

19:46.620 --> 19:47.925
What are you smiling about?

19:48.099 --> 19:49.840
-Jess, everything okay?
-[scoffs]

19:50.014 --> 19:51.538
Please don't try
to act innocent.

19:51.712 --> 19:54.149
You knew I was going
to ask him to dance,

19:54.323 --> 19:55.846
and you had Savannah ask
him first to humiliate me.

19:56.020 --> 19:57.805
No! I'd never!

19:58.371 --> 19:59.937
This isn't over, Hermione.

20:00.111 --> 20:02.897
♪ ♪

20:03.071 --> 20:05.813
Whoa. What was that?

20:05.987 --> 20:08.250
I have no idea, but we better
keep her away from Savannah.

20:09.599 --> 20:11.122
[crickets chirping]

20:11.297 --> 20:12.341
[heavy breathing]

20:13.821 --> 20:16.519
-[muffled music, chatter]
-[heavy breathing]

20:22.917 --> 20:25.920
♪ ♪

20:27.269 --> 20:29.924
-[inaudible]
-[heavy breathing]

20:33.623 --> 20:35.495
Topher: <i>
Next time on</i>Secrets
of Sulphur Springs...

20:35.669 --> 20:37.845
Zoey:
This is definitely the right
way to summon a spirit.

20:38.019 --> 20:40.282
This is our best chance
to get proof she's real.

20:40.456 --> 20:41.979
Whatever's gonna happen,
it's gonna be soon.

20:42.153 --> 20:44.068
Griffin: <i>
We cannot let Savannah
out of our sight.</i>

20:44.243 --> 20:46.027
-Harper: <i>Or my mom.
-Girl: Let's go <i>
talk to the manager.</i></i>

20:46.201 --> 20:47.420
You're not leaving this office

20:47.594 --> 20:49.248
until you tell us how
to contact your parents.

20:49.422 --> 20:51.162
Everything you do
is to get attention.

20:51.337 --> 20:53.774
"I'm not afraid of anything."

20:53.948 --> 20:55.950
-I'm not, including you.
-Jess: Yeah?

20:56.124 --> 20:58.169
Everything would be
better if you were gone.

20:58.344 --> 21:00.302
♪ ♪
